faqs:
  - title: How does Miro ensure the security of my data?
    description: >-
      Miro employs a multilayered security approach including infrastructure
      security, operational security, and product security. Data at rest is
      encrypted using AES 256-bit encryption, and data in transit is encrypted
      using TLS 1.2. Miro holds ISO 27001:2013 certification and SOC 2 Type II
      attestation.
  - title: Where is my data stored when using Miro?
    description: >-
      Under EU Data Center Residency, the compute infrastructure and all
      Customer Content (production data, backup data and metadata) is hosted
      within the EU by default. Miro offers regional data residency options,
      allowing customers to host their content in data centers located in their
      region of choice for GDPR compliance.
  - title: Does Miro use my data to train AI models?
    description: >-
      No, Miro does not use user data to train AI models. Customers can opt in
      or out of AI services, and users retain intellectual property rights to
      their AI-generated content. Miro has achieved ISO/IEC 42001:2023
      certification for AI management systems.
  - title: What security certifications does Miro hold?
    description: >-
      Miro holds several certifications including ISO 27001:2013, SOC 2 Type II,
      SOC 3, CSA CAIQ, TISAX, and ISO/IEC 42001:2023 (AI Management System).
      These certifications demonstrate Miro's commitment to maintaining high
      standards of security and compliance.
  - title: How does Miro handle data privacy and compliance?
    description: >-
      Miro complies with leading global regulations including GDPR and CCPA. The
      company offers regional data residency options and maintains comprehensive
      data protection policies. All subprocessors are contractually obligated to
      adhere to data protection standards consistent with Miro's commitments.
  - title: What subprocessors does Miro use?
    description: >-
      Miro uses Amazon Web Services (AWS) for primary cloud infrastructure with
      data residency in Ireland (EU), Ohio (US), and Sydney (AU). Microsoft
      Corporation provides accessibility services, OCR functionality, and Miro
      AI capabilities. Google LLC provides Sensitive Data Discovery through
      Enterprise Guard. Additional subprocessors include Zendesk, InSided,
      Mailchimp, Thought Industries, PartnerHero, and Gainsight for various
      support and training functions. For the complete list, visit Miro's Trust
      Center.
  - title: How often does Miro conduct security assessments?
    description: >-
      Miro conducts regular penetration testing across all components including
      external networks, web applications, mobile applications, desktop
      applications, and SDKs. The company also maintains ongoing security
      monitoring and incident response capabilities.
  - title: What security controls does Miro have in place?
    description: >-
      Miro implements comprehensive security controls including risk management
      programs, annual risk assessments, cybersecurity insurance, anti-malware
      technology, employee background checks, security awareness training,
      confidentiality agreements, whistleblower policies, mobile device
      management, and access revocation procedures upon termination.
  - title: Can I get a copy of Miro's security documentation?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro provides comprehensive security documentation through their
      Trust Center including SOC reports, ISO certificates, security policies,
      penetration test results, and architecture diagrams. These are available
      to customers upon request.
  - title: Where can I find information about Miro's uptime and downtimes?
    description: >-
      Check out Miro's Status Page at status.miro.com. This provides the ability
      to subscribe for updates, view uptimes, be notified of any outages, and
      view historical data about service availability.
  - title: Do you offer the same level of data protection to all users?
    description: >-
      Yes, regardless of which Miro plan, your data is securely managed and
      held. With TLS 1.2 or higher for transit and AES 256 at rest, in
      compliance with GDPR and CCPA standards, your data is secured to the
      highest levels at no additional cost. For advanced security controls,
      contact Miro Enterprise.
  - title: Does Miro have a bug bounty program?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro has a bug bounty program on Intigriti. Security researchers can
      participate by logging into their Intigriti account and visiting the Miro
      Intigriti program page. Submissions are handled according to program
      rules.
  - title: Can anyone at Miro access my boards?
    description: >-
      No, without your request and permission no one can view your board
      content. Miro restricts access to the production environment to a limited
      number of IP addresses and employees.
  - title: Does Miro have an Accessibility Conformance Report (ACR)?
    description: >-
      Refer to Miro's Accessibility Statement and Accessibility Article to learn
      more about Miro's accessibility features and compliance with accessibility
      standards.
  - title: Where can I find Miro's Terms and Legal documents?
    description: >-
      All of Miro's legal documents can be found at miro.com/legal/ including
      Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, Master Cloud Agreement, and other
      important legal documentation.
  - title: Does Miro use cookies?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro uses a variety of cookies and similar technologies in our
      Websites and Services to help collect Services Data. For more details
      about how these technologies are used, opt-out opportunities, and other
      options, see Miro's Cookie Policy.
  - title: Does Miro offer an API?
    description: >-
      Yes, Miro offers a comprehensive API. Visit developers.miro.com to learn
      about the capabilities of Miro's API for integration and development
      purposes.
  - title: What controls are in place for Miro AI?
    description: >-
      Miro AI has comprehensive security controls in place. Learn more about
      Miro AI security measures, data handling, and compliance through Miro's AI
      Whitepaper and related documentation.
